questions.text:
Which outputs are possible when this code runs? (fork() succeeds)

```cpp
int rc = fork();
if (rc == 0) {
    std::cout << "hello" << std::endl;
} else {
    std::cout << "world" << std::endl;
}
```

questions.explanation:
**Cooperative scheduling** trusts processes to yield the CPU voluntarily. That trust can be broken.

```
while (true) {
    // no system call, no yield()
    // OS never gets the CPU back
}
      ↑
  SYSTEM FREEZES — only fix is reboot
```

The solution: **preemptive scheduling** + a hardware timer that fires every ~10ms, forcibly giving the OS control regardless of what the process is doing.
